Introduction

Kim Minju, also known as Minju, was the lead rapper, sub-vocalist, and visual of the South Korean girl group IZ*ONE. She ranked #11 in the survival show Produce48 with 227,061 votes, earning her a spot in the group. Prior to joining the show, Minju appeared in dramas such as The Great Seducer (2018) and in music videos such as iKON's "#WYD" and Kriesha Chu's "Like Paradise."

She made her debut as a member of IZ*ONE on October 29, 2018, with their first mini album "COLOR*IZ".

On April 29, 2021, IZ*ONE disbanded after their contract of two years and six months ended.

Following IZ*ONE's disbandment, Minju has since focused on acting and being an MC for "Show! Music Core."
